```

## Pixel Art Styling

All components must follow the pixel art rules:
- Square corners only (no rounded)
- Banded colors (no gradients)
- Pixel fonts (Press Start 2P/VT323)
- Touch targets minimum 44px
- Grid-aligned layouts

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All 6 zone components implemented
- [ ] All overlay components implemented
- [ ] Each component has test file with state previews
- [ ] Pixel art styling applied (no rounded corners, no gradients)
- [ ] Color palette imported from `types/colors.ts` (no hardcoded colors)
- [ ] Touch targets verified (44px minimum)
- [ ] Components render at 360640 without scroll

## Dependencies
**BLOCKS ON:** 
- TYPE-Foundation (need types)
- SETUP-Base (need React + Tailwind set up)

## Notes
- Consider adding Storybook later for visual testing
- For now, use test files with different state snapshots
- Use CSS Grid for the main layout (6 zones)

# TypeScript Type System Foundation

**Priority:** P0 (Blocks almost everything else)

## Overview
Define ALL TypeScript types/interfaces for the entire game. This is the foundation that all other systems depend on.

## Types to Define

### 1. Core Game State
```typescript
interface GameState {
  day: number;
  phase: 'open-operation' | 'selective-enforcement' | 'procedural-conflict' | 'constraint-saturation';
  visible: VisibleState;
  hidden: HiddenState;
}
```

### 2. Visible State (Player-Facing)
```typescript
interface VisibleState {
  popularity: PopularityLevel;    // 'very-low' | 'low' | 'medium' | 'high' | 'very-high'
  meltOMeter: HeatLevel;          // 'calm' | 'watched' | 'tense' | 'critical'
  communitySupport: SupportLevel; // 'none' | 'low' | 'medium' | 'high' | 'very-high'
  staffRoster: WorkerId[];
  featuredFlavor: WorkerId;
}
```

### 3. Hidden State (System-Only)
```typescript
interface HiddenState {
  visibility: number;              // 0-100
  workerRiskProfiles: Record<WorkerId, number>;
  customerArchetypeDrift: ArchetypeState;
  agentAggressionProfile: AggressionLevel;
  documentationQuality: DocQuality;
  legitimacyThresholds: LegitimacyState;
}
```

### 4. Workers/Flavors
```typescript
type WorkerId = 'vanilla' | 'chocolate' | 'strawberry' | 'butter-pecan' | 'pistachio' | 'cotton-candy';

interface Worker {
  id: WorkerId;
  name: string;
  status: 'present' | 'featured' | 'stepped-back' | 'removed' | 'unavailable';
  symbolicWeight: number;  // 1-10, affects protest effectiveness
}
```

### 5. Agents & Encounters
```typescript
interface AgentEncounter {
  targetWorker: WorkerId;
  documentation: Documentation;
  aggressionProfile: AggressionLevel;
  steps: EncounterStep[];
}

type DocumentationQuality = 'none' | 'incomplete' | 'incorrect' | 'correct' | 'comprehensive';
```

### 6. Customers & Queue
```typescript
interface Customer {
  id: string;
  archetype: CustomerArchetype;
  preferredFlavor?: WorkerId;
  willSignPetition: boolean;
  reactionToRemove: Record<WorkerId, ReactionType>;
}

type CustomerArchetype = 'regular' | 'nervous' | 'enthusiastic' | 'suspicious' | 'solidarity';
```

### 7. Community & Resistance
```typescript
interface ResistanceState {
  petitionsCollected: number;
  protestsAttended: number;
  documentationRequestsFiled: number;
  equipmentBansActive: EquipmentBan[];
  communityDefenseUses: number;
}
```

### 8. UI State Types
```typescript
interface UIState {
  currentZone: GameZone;
  activeOverlay: OverlayType | null;
  dialogueQueue: DialogueLine[];
  menuState: MenuState;
}

type GameZone = 'power-ups' | 'queue' | 'meltometer' | 'counter' | 'roster' | 'menu';
type OverlayType = 'encounter' | 'dialogue' | 'document' | 'summary' | 'protest' | 'recovery';
```

### 9. Color Palette Types
```typescript
interface ColorPalette {
  powerUp: { primary: string; secondary: string; accent: string; };
  queue: { primary: string; secondary: string; accent: string; };
  meltOMeter: { low: string; medium: string; high: string; };
  counter: { primary: string; secondary: string; accent: string; };
  menu: { background: string; border: string; text: string; };
  dialogue: { background: string; text: string; };
  background: { primary: string; secondary: string; };
  text: { primary: string; secondary: string; };
}
```

## File Structure
```
src/types/
 index.ts           # Re-exports all types
 core.ts            # GameState, core interfaces
 workers.ts         # Worker, WorkerId, worker-related
 encounters.ts      # Agent, Documentation, Encounter types
 customers.ts       # Customer, Queue, Archetype types
 resistance.ts      # Petition, Protest, Community Defense
 ui.ts              # UIState, Overlay, Zone types
 colors.ts          # ColorPalette (single source of truth)
 constants.ts       # Game constants, initial state
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All types defined with strict TypeScript (no `any`)
- [ ] Single source of truth for color palette in `types/colors.ts`
- [ ] Initial game state exportable from `types/constants.ts`
- [ ] All types exportable from `types/index.ts`
- [ ] JSDoc comments on all exported interfaces
- [ ] No circular type dependencies

## Dependencies
**NONE** - This is the foundation

## Blocks
- Game Engine
- UI Components
- Content System

# Testing Infrastructure

**Priority:** P2
**Dependencies:** SETUP-Base (can work in parallel)

## Overview
Set up comprehensive testing infrastructure for the game. Each component must be testable in isolation with state previews.

## Testing Stack
- **Unit Tests:** Vitest (comes with SETUP)
- **Component Tests:** React Testing Library
- **Coverage:** Vitest coverage
